HEADWORD: Gallipot
<hw>Gal"li*pot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. OD.
<ets>gleypot</ets>, the first part of which is possibly akin to E.
<ets>glad</ets>. See <er>Glad</er>, and <er>Pot</er>.]</ety> <def>A
glazed earthen pot or vessel, used by druggists and apothecaries for
containing medicines, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gallium</ent>⟦br⟧
